# Example line the bootstrap tool appends to the LOCAL machine's
# ~/.ssh/authorized_keys (Windows: %USERPROFILE%\.ssh\authorized_keys).
#
# This is the public key of the key pair that lives ON THE SERVER and that
# Claude / Codex uses to SSH back into the local machine through the tunnel.
#
# The options restrict what this key can do:
#   from="127.0.0.1,::1"   only accepted when the connection arrives from
#                          loopback, i.e. only through the reverse tunnel —
#                          never directly from LAN / internet
#   no-agent-forwarding    no SSH agent forwarding
#   no-X11-forwarding      no X11 forwarding

from="127.0.0.1,::1",no-agent-forwarding,no-X11-forwarding ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIExampleExampleExampleExampleExampleExampl user@server
